The paper discusses the security risks in the supply chain of IoT devices, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a risk assessment framework, which involves analyzing the reliability of the system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the impact of supplier grouping, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
